column5: This little fellow was caught a few weeks ago in the Middle Kenai while I was in Alaska. Size was 39 7/8 X 23 3/4 and using the typical formula comes out to a hair over 28 pounds!!! Unfortunately it wasn't I who got to catch it.
WOW! Beauty! And from shore right in front of the cabin too! Thanks for sharing that. Now get working on your report, Mr.!
Drifter_016,  That's it? LOL.  Great fish dude.  -Sawyer
Not sure Im ready for one of them on the pin yet Dave.  What a beaut.  TFS
yes he is quite wee   WOW!
I opened the thread in hopes that i would see a tiny trout.....I feel like my time was wasted
Man that is small...  Actually, no it isn't... What a fish! My fly rod just snapped even thinking about a fish like that.
Beauty!  I saw the title and was going to skip it...then I saw it was Drifter....where you live and fish, I'm quite happy with what you call "wee"
